The '''electricity sector in Singapore''' ranges from [[electricity generation|generation]], [[electric power transmission|transmission]], [[electric power distribution|distribution]] and [[electricity market|retailing]] of [[electricity]] in [[Singapore]].
==Regulator== [[File:Singapore Power Building 4, Aug 07.JPG|thumb|[[Singapore Power]] office in [[Singapore Power Building]]]]
Electricity sector in Singapore is regulated by [[Singapore Power]] ({{zh|t=新加坡能源有限公司}}).
==Generation== ===Power stations=== [[File:Senoko Power Station.JPG|thumb|[[Senoko Power Station]], the largest power station in Singapore]]
{{main|List of power stations in Singapore}}
===Fuel=== As of 2015, Singapore uses [[natural gas]] (95%) and waste (4%) for power stations' fuel. [[Oil]] used to contribute 23% in 2005 but now is down to 1%.<ref> [http://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/from-the-straits-times-archives-singapore-opts-for-cleaner-energy-sources Singapore opts for cleaner energy sources] </ref> The fossil fuel basis of Singapore's electricity system affects the way that electric cars are taxed.<ref>[https://www.cnbc.com/2016/03/08/tesla-model-s-owner-protests-singapores-carbon-emissions-surcharge.html Tesla Model S owner protests Singapore's carbon emissions surcharge]</ref><ref>[http://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/transport/tesla-boss-calls-pm-lee-over-co2-levy Tesla boss calls PM Lee over CO2 levy]</ref>
