'''''Aramco World''''' (formerly ''Saudi Aramco World'') is a bi-monthly magazine published by [[Aramco Services Company]], a US-based subsidiary of [[Saudi Aramco]], the state-owned oil company of the Kingdom of [[Saudi Arabia]]. The first issue of the magazine appeared in November 1949.<ref>{{cite news|author1=William Tracy|title=Aramco World Turns 50|url=http://archive.aramcoworld.com/issue/199906/aramco.world.turns.50.htm|accessdate=28 September 2015|work=Aramco World|issue=50 (6)|date=December 1999}}</ref> The bimonthly magazine is published in [[Houston, Texas]].

While Saudi Arabia is still frequently the main feature of articles, the magazine also covers the wider Arabic and Muslim world, and is aimed at both company employees and other interested readers. The website also allows free access to back issues going back to the early 1960s, including photography.<ref>[http://www.intute.ac.uk/artsandhumanities/cgi-bin/fullrecord.pl?handle=humbul16167 Saudi Aramco World] (from [[Intute]], Retrieved 12 May 2007)</ref>

In 2004, the magazine's website was awarded "Best Magazine Website" by the [[Web Marketing Association]].

