{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2015}} {{Use Australian English|date=January 2015}} {{Infobox power station | name = Stockyard Hill Wind Farm | name_official = | image = | image_size = | image_caption = | image_alt = | location_map = Australia | location_map_size = | location_map_caption = | coordinates = {{coord|37|32|9|S|143|15|5|E|type:landmark|display=inline,title}} | coordinates_ref = | country = | location = | status = U | construction_began = May 2018 | commissioned = | decommissioned = | cost = | owner = [[Origin Energy]] | operator = [[Goldwind Australia]] | ps_units_operational = | ps_units_planned = 149 | ps_units_manu_model = | wind_hub_height = | wind_rotor_diameter = | wind_rated_speed = | wind_farm_type = | wind_site_elevation = | wind_site_usage = | wind_site_area = | ps_electrical_capacity = 530 [[Megawatt|MW]] | ps_electrical_cap_fac = | website = {{url|https://www.stockyardhillwindfarm.com.au/}} | extra = }} '''Stockyard Hill Wind Farm''' is a wind farm project being developed and constructed [[Origin Energy|by Goldwind Australia]], in [[Victoria (Australia)]].
The proposed facility will have 149 wind turbines at a site approximately 35&nbsp;km west of [[Ballarat]] between [[Beaufort, Victoria|Beaufort]] and [[Skipton, Victoria|Skipton]].<ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.weeklytimesnow.com.au/news/national/stockyard-hill-wind-farm-to-go-ahead-origin-energy-says/story-fnkfnspy-1226833627252| title=Stockyard Hill wind farm to go ahead, Origin Energy says| date=21 February 2014| first=Chris| last=McLennan}}</ref> The forecast cost is $900 million ($750 million US dollars)<ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.businessspectator.com.au/news/2014/2/21/wind-power/origin-shelves-wind-farm-pending-review| title=Origin shelves wind farm, pending review| date=21 February 2014| publisher=Climate Spectator}}</ref> In December 2009, the original plan for 242 turbines, the plan was changed to only have 157 turbines. The Victorian minister of planning approved the 157 turbines, in October 2010.<ref name="Stockyard">{{cite web| url=http://www.stockyardhillwindfarm.com.au/ | title=Stockyard Hill Wind Farm| publisher=Origin}}</ref>
In 2013 Origin contemplated selling the project before production would have begun, but decided to continue the project.<ref>{{cite news| url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-01-15/origin-decides-to-hold-onto-stockyard-hill-wind-farm-in-victoria.html| title=Origin drops sale of Stockyard| date=15 January 2013| first=James| last=Paton| publisher=Bloomberg}}</ref>
Construction commenced in May 2018 on a design that has 149 wind turbines. [[Origin Energy]] has a power purchase agreement to buy all electricity until 2030. [[Goldwind Australia]] is providing [[Engineering, Procurement and Construction]] during development and Warranty, Operations and Maintenance services following commissioning.<ref name="Stockyard"/>
