The '''Ukishima Solar Power Plant''' (浮島太陽光発電所) is a 7 MW solar [[photovoltaic power station]] located on the waterfront in [[Kawasaki, Kanagawa|Kawasaki]]. It is the first solar plant built by [[Tokyo Electric Power Company|Tepco]], and was completed on August 10, 2011. In the first year of operation, it produced 9,453 MWh, a [[capacity factor]] of 0.15,<ref>[http://www.tepco.co.jp/en/news/topics/images/120810a.pdf Monthly Total]</ref> which was about 30% greater than anticipated.<ref>[http://www.tepco.co.jp/en/news/topics/1211710_2266.html First Anniversary of Ukishima Solar Power Station, One of the Largest Solar Power Stations in Japan Located in the Coastal Area of Kawasaki City]</ref> An unusual feature of the plant is that the panels are mounted at a fixed angle of 10°, instead of the 30°, which would normally be considered optimal for this latitude.<ref>[http://www.tepco.co.jp/en/challenge/energy/megasolar/index-e.html Tepco real time monitor]</ref>

